      "writtenOn": "2020-08-03T13:19:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do you have some other examples?\nIn general, Tast prefers Go functions, rather than command line, if possible.\nE.g., os.Stat/Lstat will be preferred than \"ls\". os.Mkdirs() is preferred than \"mkdir\" etc.\n\nI understand that it is not the main focus of this section itself, and ls is just an example. However, regardless of the focus, I imagine it could be confusing that the way written in the example is not a recommended approach, specifically for the engs who\u0027re new to tast,",
